 2015 |access-date=August 10, 2015}}</ref>\n* [[Simon Quarterman]] as Lee Sizemore, Westworld's narrative director, whose artistic temperament aggravates his co-workers.<ref name=\"casting_aug6\" /> In season 3, Quarterman portrays a digital replica of Lee Sizemore in a simulation.\n* [[Rodrigo Santoro]] as Hector Escaton (seasons 1\u20132, guest season 3), a host. He is a wanted gang leader bent on robbing the Mariposa Hotel in Sweetwater.<ref name=\"Nerdist-July 30\">{{Cite web |url=http://nerdist.com/westworld-gets-a-premiere-date-and-tons-of-new-details-at-last/ |title=WESTWORLD Gets a Premiere Date and TONS of New Details (at Last!) |last=Lutes |first=Alicia |date=July 30, 2016 |website=Nerdist |url-status=dead |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160731213934/http://nerdist.com/westworld-gets-a-premiere-date-and-tons-of-new-details-at-last/ |archive-date=July 31, 2016 |access-date=August 2, 2016}}</ref> In season 3, Santoro portrays Ettore, a host character of Warworld, in a simulation.\n* [[Angela Sarafyan]] as Clementine Pennyfeather (seasons 1\u20132), a host. She works as a prostitute for Maeve and is one of Westworld's most popular attractions.<ref name=\"casting_aug6\" />\n* [[Shannon Woodward]] as Elsie Hughes (seasons 1\u20132), a rising star in the Programming Division tasked with remedying odd behavior in the park's hosts.<ref name=\"Nerdist-July 30\" />\n* [[Ed Harris]] as the Man in Black,<!-- NOTE: Per the \"RfC on Potential Spoilers\" discussion from the article talk page, consensus stands opposed to adding the major reveal about the Man in Black to this section. Please consult the article talk page if you wish to challenge any of this. --> a sadistic veteran guest attempting to uncover Westworld's innermost secrets.<ref name=\"harris\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ed-harris-set-as-key-724626 |title=Ed Harris Set as Key Villain in HBO's 'Westworld' |last=Goldberg |first=Lesley |date=August 11, 2014 |website=The Hollywood Reporter |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140812064011/http://www.hollywoodreporter.com/live-feed/ed-harris-set-as-key-724626 |archive-date=August 12, 2014 |access-date=August 12, 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Anthony Hopkins]] as Doctor Robert Ford (seasons 1\u20132), the co-founder and Park Director of Westworld.<ref name=\"hopkins_wood\" />\n* [[Ben Barnes (actor)|Ben Barnes]] as Logan Delos (season 1, recurring season 2), a regular guest who introduces William to the park.<ref name=\"ew-july20\">{{Cite web |url=http://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/20/westworld-ben-barnes |title=Westworld casting switch: Narnia star replacing Once Upon actor |last=Hibberd |first=James |date=July 20, 2015 |website=Entertainment Weekly |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150722171352/http://www.ew.com/article/2015/07/20/westworld-ben-barnes |archive-date=July 22, 2015 |access-date=July 20, 2015}}</ref> In season 2, Barnes also portrays an embodiment of The Forge, a large database containing guests' data.\n* [[Clifton Collins Jr.]] as Lawrence Gonzales (seasons 1\u20132) / El Lazo (season 1), a host. He is a charming but dangerous outlaw with a knack for maneuvering and negotiating the various criminal elements of Westworld.<ref name=\"ew.com\" />\n* [[Jimmi Simpson]] as William (season 1, recurring season 2),<!-- NOTE: Per the \"RfC on Potential Spoilers\" discussion from the article talk page, consensus stands opposed to adding the major reveal about William to this section. Please consult the article talk page if you wish to challenge any of this. --> a reluctant first-time visitor to Westworld, joining his future brother-in-law, Logan. Initially dismissive of the park's more lascivious attractions, he slowly uncovers a deeper meaning to the park's narrative.<ref name=\"ew.com\" />\n* [[Tessa Thompson]] as Charlotte Hale, Executive Director of the Delos Destinations Board, which oversees Westworld and other parks.<ref>{{Cite web |url